Class BCLLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluefire.bclreader.publicclasses.BCLLocation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<BCLLocation>

    public class BCLLocation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<BCLLocation>
    A BCLLocation object represents a location within a book. A location can represent either a single location or a range that has a beginning and end.

    • Constructor Detail

      • BCLLocation

        public BCLLocation(java.lang.String idref,
                   java.lang.String cfi)
        Creates a location. A location is initially created by a BCLReaderView instance. An application may wish to create a location manually for use with a BCLHighlight object. A location's CFI is considered to be a "partial" CFI because it doesn't include a reference to a spine item.
        Parameters:
        idref - The associated spine item's idref.
        cfi - The partial canonical fragment identifier.
